snippet.textDisplay:
Two of my sibling's wife's bought a Peloton. They use it weekly, my brother's use it weekly, and I use it when I go to their house's.

The problem is presentation. Everyone seems to worry about sexism, but while individually that occurs which side is sexist? One could get it for themselves and find their SO wanting to try it. Or, could hint at wanting it, so your SO gets it, or could be gifted from the family. I haven't seen the whole commercial, but I do know to jump to assumptions makes an A$$ out of you and me.

This type of thing shouldn't be taken literally. If you want literal, then look to history and culture. Thats what determines social ideology.
